title._content: Sen. Languth, C.N. McArthur & wife, Gov. Withycombe & wife, Chf. [i.e., Chief] Justice Moore, W.L. Thompson  (LOC)

description._content: Bain News Service,, publisher. Sen. Languth, C.N. McArthur & wife, Gov. Withycombe & wife, Chf. [i.e., Chief] Justice Moore, W.L. Thompson [1915 Jan. 12] 1 negative : glass ; 5 x 7 in. or smaller. Notes: Title from data provided by the Bain News Service on the negative. Photograph shows politician James Withycombe (1854-1919), who served as Governor of Oregon with his wife, Isabel (Carpenter) Withycombe; Clifton Nesmith McArthur (1879-1923), U.S. Representative from Oregon; and Oregon Chief Justice Frank A. Moore (1844 -1918). Photograph probably taken on day of Withycombe's inauguration as governor of Oregon on January 12, 1915, outside the State Capitol in Salem, Oregon. Forms part of: George Grantham Bain Collection (Library of Congress). Format: Glass negatives. Rights Info: No known restrictions on publication. Repository: Library of Congress, Prints and Photographs Division, Washington, D.C. 20540 USA, hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/pp.print General information about the Bain Collection is available at hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/pp.ggbain Higher resolution image is available (Persistent URL): hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/ggbain.18268 Call Number: LC-B2- 3363-13
